&lt;p&gt;Data Quality &amp; Assurance Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity for a well organised and self-motivated team member to join the medicine health care group management team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Princess Alexandra NHS Hospital Trust is committed to excellent data quality for all patient pathways. All patients are recorded on our electronic patient system COSMIS and to manage each patients journey from referral to treatment, we need to ensure that data is entered accurately in a timely and efficient manner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Main duties of the job&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be working to improve the quality of data on our patient administration system and work with the healthcare group to produce reports on data quality issues. The post would suit individuals who are confident in the use of Microsoft Office and have a good working knowledge of Patient Administration Systems, and associated operational processes in outpatients and inpatient care, but NHS experience is not essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Knowledge of COSMIC would be an advantage and a sound understanding of the Referral to Treatment Standard.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact Ayse Casey on ayse.casey@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
